                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/122.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Jefferson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Presidential party and myself left Tuesday on United States ship <hi
                        rend="italic">Chattanooga</hi> on trip of inspection of Fonseca Bay and
                    returned to Managua today. Trip a very instructive one and President Díaz
                    expressed himself as being unusually pleased with the opportunity of visiting
                    this much-discussed region and with the courtesy and hospitality of Captain
                    Senn. Nicaraguan people in general seem to be deeply interested in the trip and
                    greeted cordially on the way. I shall report in detail by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
